<h3>Positive Prompt <small>(or just "Prompt")</small></h3>
<p>
	For prompts, there are two schools of thought, which can be mixed: keyword and sentence.
</p>
<p>
    <code>2 girls playing at the river</code>
	or
	<code>2girls, playing, river</code>
</p>
<p>
	What do you need to use? Simple : look what the creator of your model said is better to use.
</p>

<h4>It’s totally possible to mix them. For example</h4>	
<pre class="not-prose"><code>(best quality, masterpiece:1.2), (2 girls running outside:1.1), blue sportwear, joyful, happy, open mouth,  sweat, (hot:1.1), sun</code></pre>

<p>
	The order of your keywords is important. The further your keyword is from the beginning, the less powerful it is.
</p>

